From BSP-229
{quote}
but I'd like to be able to get some numbers from it, such as number of unit tests ran (already available in Bamboo) and coverage percentage from Clover
{quote}

This feature request is to add, more options/data to the Javascript widgets on top of the ones [currently provided|http://confluence.atlassian.com/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=14286945]

Specifically, ability to add/embed build resutts - unit tests run, build history and results for given build, as per BSP-229

Under certain circumstances (e.g. initial builds) the SVN changes are not being picked up by Bamboo. One possible scenario where this occurrence is prevalent is on initial builds after changing source repository as discussed in [BSP-211|https://support.atlassian.com/browse/BSP-211]
{quote}
Here's the scenario I am looking at;
1. Create a plan with manual builds only and set source control to use tag TAG_1
2. Do the build
3. Edit the configuration for this plan and choose the tag TAG_2
4. Do the build
{quote}

Bamboo adds a duplicate path variable, when executing builds in Windows

Below is the output of my ant task, which invokes a batch file to spit out all the defined system environment variables.
{code:log}
Path=C:\Program Files\Java\jrockit-R27.3.1-jre1.5.0_11\bin;C:\Program Files\Java\jrockit-R27.3.1-jre1.5.0_11\bin;C:\WINDOWS\system32;C:\WINDOWS;C:\WINDOWS\System32\Wbem;C:\Program Files\apache-ant-1.7.0\bin;C:\Program Files\Subversion\bin;
PATH=C:\Program Files\Java\jrockit-R27.3.1-jre1.5.0_11\bin;
{code}

The PATH added by Bamboo is wrong, since the PATH variable itself is case sensitive. This may cause weirdness in builds which rely on PATH variable being set.

